The consortium partners will develop and execute a long-term science and innovation strategy for the CoE ñbased on a SWOT analysis of NCBJñ that focuses on two strategic research and innovation topics:

ï Novel high-temperature, corrosion and radiation resistant materials for industrial applications; 
ï Novel radiopharmaceutical materials for medical applications.

The consortium partners believe that leveraging their combined research and innovation capabilities will:

ï Enable more efficient usage of their research infrastructure and equipment;
ï Create more attractive opportunities to educate and train young researchers;
ï Foster an innovation ecosystem that increases technology-transfer for industrial and medical applications;
ï Create the critical mass to win more competitive research funding.
